<p local-id=3D"12d08fb1-ac4b-4f76-b775-fd417110f792"><strong>Reference JSON=
 Schema for the recipe data model</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"8b447d53-8595-4b3e-81f2-047202943a7d">
<li local-id=3D"f26f7ff2-0095-4ded-b7ad-281823e9e52d">
<p local-id=3D"4aec5867-e87d-4a60-b08c-2c19ce6e1015">Preview (DRAFT) - <img=
 height=3D"250" style=3D"margin: 2px; border: 1px solid #ddd; box-sizing: b=
order-box; vertical-align: text-bottom;" src=3D"4193697c1305a144b39d14ea228=
bf9508d0a767c6a04088a103c19a8f4973628" width=3D"250"></p></li>
</ul>
<h1 local-id=3D"e11174cd-815b-4658-9d68-61e148a90fb3" id=3D"AIEnablement-Co=
nnectorsMetadataStandarization-ChallengesandConsiderations">Challenges and =
Considerations</h1>
<p local-id=3D"f535a8cd-1768-448b-a0f0-ad8596875885">Here is a summary of e=
xisting limitation and constraints which needs to be addressed to unblock t=
he full potential of all connectivity related capabilities, enabled for AI.=
</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"5a303193-d4c7-4bae-9b38-e61f94c81db5" id=3D"AIEnablement-Co=
nnectorsMetadataStandarization-ResourceModels/Schema">Resource Models/Schem=
a</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"54b38957-09d9-4486-8fcd-3819ec658e9f">
<li local-id=3D"05fdce67-4dc2-4788-be72-f1907904ffe8">
<p local-id=3D"f33f7461-c8ef-4505-bdfa-2a50691cb5d2">Inconsistency in schem=
a on how applications and account definitions are stored across frameworks.=
 Effort needs to be made to standardized and adopt above changes, for metad=
ata consistency.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"680146c3-1b58-48bf-867c-b03618ad50bd">
<p local-id=3D"ebec7646-be62-49b2-be57-bf844a7fe155">Adapters and CloudStre=
ams framework do not directly expose JSONSchema for its interaction definit=
ions. There is an internal utility on Workflow UI, to convert the Input/Out=
put signature in proprietary webMethods document schema definition into JSO=
NSchema, during saving of a workflow definition.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"de13302e-bd5a-4ad0-bd51-d62360373043" id=3D"AIEnablement-Co=
nnectorsMetadataStandarization-DataSanitization">Data Sanitization</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"9f7bcb8c-ef78-476c-b729-45d58a64e7f4">
<li local-id=3D"02e63db9-51fc-4268-a799-f3cb859a8155">
<p local-id=3D"3c5fa2a2-1126-4aa7-ab6c-d90f82c57345">Data Quality - name, l=
abel/title, description for connectors, actions/triggers, and field paramet=
ers. Requires data correction, populating missing information, etc.</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"3f2c7fec-3752-4f50-817f-34a4f440b0c3">
<p local-id=3D"1b5a2665-d42b-4a16-ab7e-bccfa53b4f42">There will be effort r=
equired across all connectors, to embed and return description in language =
and grammar suitable for LLM to interpret. Not all information is readily a=
vailable in a single place to consolidate and wrapped across all flavors of=
 connectors.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c26623ac-6276-402e-864a-0601115b7bc0">
<p local-id=3D"5a17f4fd-d978-467f-8757-787219d208b2">Duplicate connector de=
finitions - there are multiple connectors with implementation coming from v=
arious frameworks and overlapping functionalities. It needs to be non-ambig=
uous for AI to pick and choose.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b15466ab-55c6-4c73-9ef8-98a45b5dce59">
<p local-id=3D"4b973993-8cb1-4820-8df3-5b127ebb633e">Multiple Versions agai=
nst a single connector.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"647d2f85-8ac5-4e7a-b05a-4cd4303f0c09" id=3D"AIEnablement-Co=
nnectorsMetadataStandarization-SupportforCustomConnectors,Operations">Suppo=
rt for Custom Connectors, Operations</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"9a0b26db-e668-4354-ba5a-effd0d09973d">
<li local-id=3D"bcea865a-8dd6-4878-8eac-8918a3c18e74">
<p local-id=3D"aaf5a6e4-ead0-4648-b098-dd3a1eb2b948">Using the above =E2=80=
=98interaction template=E2=80=99 flow requires more refinement from respect=
ive teams and user-journey. It is critical functionality for both Adapters/=
CloudStreams based applications, offering maximum flexibility for defining =
an operation, based on their requirement.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"e602f94f-aaf6-421e-8376-0ae7ecac3a9c" id=3D"AIEnablement-Co=
nnectorsMetadataStandarization-NamespaceChangesImpact">Namespace Changes Im=
pact</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"63ddcbf7-ccd1-4de7-939a-914a4937d77a">
<li local-id=3D"492adfb5-5126-4712-b6f9-bea7a4335a70">
<p local-id=3D"9b210890-2445-4081-b811-a4d586a572ad">CloudStreams Connector=
s use connector definitions with its identifier using =E2=80=98softwareag=
=E2=80=99 in its names. The upcoming namespace changes will impact the defi=
nitions/metadata.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"e4053705-de75-4c9c-85d7-c1a79c9f2250" id=3D"AIEnablement-Co=
nnectorsMetadataStandarization-Pre-definedOperationavailability">Pre-define=
d Operation availability</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"63575c38-1bac-41ff-8596-e369be9d9b9d">
<li local-id=3D"ae1ac812-937e-4d4f-8ee4-7b70a5235c06">
<p local-id=3D"0661aa8a-64b8-43ce-9f24-4ed35bfa95c6">The current set of pre=
-defined operations are only a select few those are created by the connecto=
r team, to pre-bundle with the connector. These do not reflect all the avai=
lable functionality and are suitable only for working with standard objects=
.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"708f6d03-cd02-4069-8b4f-43f093da6d6c">
<p local-id=3D"c0cc2408-0081-4066-bd77-d61c9e08e63a">The current set of pre=
-defined operations in CloudStreams are only available for Workflow and Flo=
w Cloud and written in to-be deprecated provider extension packages. This i=
s not universally available for Cloud Anywhere (DADA) or on-premises use-ca=
ses.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"c6dd4d5c-4f8a-4940-a60f-32a3ef4182fd" id=3D"AIEnablement-Co=
nnectorsMetadataStandarization-WorkflowDefinitionEnhancement">Workflow Defi=
nition Enhancement</h2>
<p local-id=3D"3b865233-6659-4fd5-a831-7130c112c967">The workflow definitio=
n contains embeddings which are either obsolete, redundant or irrelevant fo=
r a workflow definition.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"c134c1fd-b8a4-4cfd-accc-f6e82e3741f5">
<li local-id=3D"c39a6d37-421b-4bf1-8251-be2e71f9d165">
<p local-id=3D"7f7e6d4a-7831-4e7d-9037-03fcd5e7562a">The current workflow d=
efinition holds framework and connector specific schema and information. Fo=
r example, there are separate definitions for adapters, cloudstreams connec=
tor, nodejs connectors, which are embedded under =E2=80=98action_schema=E2=
=80=99.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"762445a6-5c85-4b53-8c60-1e733715c49f">
<p local-id=3D"88a03315-e995-4206-a50f-ac134749c1ee">The =E2=80=98usage=E2=
=80=99 section within a workflow definition refers to href like =E2=86=92 <=
code>https://flowdocs.built.io/concepts/conditions</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4985c53a-1ac8-4b0f-8abe-8e25461c9452">
<p local-id=3D"c6fe4abc-079b-41e8-b74f-ad1db3a3756e">Besides the applicatio=
n metadata, the controls, utilities, IoT, advance logic (custom NodeJS code=
 reference) needs to be available for construction of complete workflow def=
inition. As long as these definitions are available via APIs and referencea=
ble, it can help construct the final definition.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"a0cffb69-8c10-4f27-b391-4cc34a87d5a3" id=3D"AIEnablement-Co=
nnectorsMetadataStandarization-AssetAvailabilityScopes">Asset Availability =
Scopes</h2>
<p local-id=3D"69c87ef8-8202-477e-a6e4-fb14d733078e">In terms of availabili=
ty and re-use of resources, it can be classified under following scopes.</p=
>
<ul local-id=3D"eb222b23-ca63-4183-9637-ada2ac1591ac">
<li local-id=3D"9989d8f2-5b93-4135-8985-cd0647ec19f3">
<p local-id=3D"8e5c3ec3-3c3a-411a-b08f-b7880c15b140">Global Scope</p>
<ul local-id=3D"ad5e6614-d366-48b7-ad92-0e0e140b6395">
<li local-id=3D"40975466-f983-4846-921a-3a5e9f2bdcc5">
<p local-id=3D"7f7db39c-cc3a-446a-88d1-ebb870722629">Applications (pre-bund=
led)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"34cddbe8-2172-4db2-9ac5-07f44f89764d">
<p local-id=3D"43ecd226-b54e-4d9c-8883-d478c2160112">Actions (pre-defined)<=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4fc5e54f-8127-4cf7-b3db-eb9c19c83b8d">
<p local-id=3D"6e328ef6-a78f-4e43-a35a-954442541a44">Triggers (available fo=
r workflow definition)</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"748617cd-a4ca-4382-8a05-f867b32e2fc7">
<p local-id=3D"80a0dae6-a7e2-4b8b-99c7-3cd45eb6dfc0">Tenant Scope</p>
<ul local-id=3D"d031f977-74c8-42a7-b594-a66bf6909d7f">
<li local-id=3D"30f16f44-0889-4182-b8ad-5f4eae61f4ba">
<p local-id=3D"6e091d50-41d1-4550-9301-f3f5838950c7">Applications (user-def=
ined) - cli-based connectors, CloudStreams based connectors (restricted)</p=
></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"2daa5725-e9f4-45cc-96bc-1e07fffc12b2">
<p local-id=3D"d632bbf8-17e3-48ab-8b87-a7755faad59a">Project Scope</p>
<ul local-id=3D"b659758b-20a5-4f16-8e2e-149083ea9013">
<li local-id=3D"a5d6a7cb-dfcc-46ee-86bd-cef2a8c8ff83">
<p local-id=3D"381c2d1b-5796-4e33-b69d-12105f0e8296">Applications (user-def=
ined REST/SOAP connectors) - native web-service and CloudStreams based conn=
ector</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"52fe568b-1ddc-42b9-be38-3a23ccb376b2">
<p local-id=3D"7afbed27-afcf-4216-b0b1-a93adebc7ca7">Accounts</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7202872a-035b-459d-8b45-2c681ed48470">
<p local-id=3D"74ac1ab0-d680-48be-8d78-3e57905b1d5e">Actions</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0e38a990-0edd-4206-8942-a9a5bb181d3e">
<p local-id=3D"300858bc-157a-400c-af6c-6a82af523d80">Workflows</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b0fa7393-fc59-4df7-ba66-05870acb48b5">
<p local-id=3D"6b1cbf20-d20f-407b-9fb7-f1bbac82983a">Flow Cloud (Only on WM=
IO)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f804959e-1158-4a87-b826-527ed4448528">
<p local-id=3D"bc2b1403-a28c-43ed-aedb-b756bf61ae1a">Flow Anywhere (Develop=
 Anywhere Deploy Anywhere)</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"db225fd6-6816-4491-9596-64ef66ef9bcc">
<p local-id=3D"daf9a6de-9283-4c1b-9b62-43ec41c29d59">Workflow Scope</p>
<ul local-id=3D"37329b50-2c89-4c9b-b028-6afc80060027">
<li local-id=3D"202413db-5b8a-490a-a58b-8339fc1fced1">
<p local-id=3D"63917632-62f6-480e-a97f-ea3a36a922d6">Applications (usage re=
ference)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cb2015b0-8de0-4d40-8f7e-4f6b92400d18">
<p local-id=3D"43d03c18-10f6-4dbd-ab0a-c6fb7c95e681">Accounts (usage refere=
nce)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b2d771ae-a713-40f5-a0cb-feb5246dc139">
<p local-id=3D"bb6e0440-9ae5-4237-a703-f041e8d523d4">Actions (user-configur=
ed)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d7dccf54-ec64-4b11-9a64-256ddff66447">
<p local-id=3D"36f75426-a5b7-48f4-b673-d392a9395cef">Triggers (user-configu=
red)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4375241a-2730-4f97-b43f-a8c3055b4767">
<p local-id=3D"14f33a74-3ef6-4cf9-add1-78fc9e5ddcbf">Other nodes (user-conf=
igured)</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p local-id=3D"bd5bb960-6e4d-41ba-b8c1-792a652903cd">NOTE: This requires co=
nfirmation across all asset owners and teams for defining appropriate APIs,=
 for introspection, required by AI for deriving context.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h1 local-id=3D"d042d628-52dd-41bd-aa20-a6c663008076" id=3D"AIEnablement-Co=
nnectorsMetadataStandarization-DeveloperTools(Internal)">Developer Tools (I=
nternal)</h1>
<p local-id=3D"5c4dad71-505a-46ac-88f9-732455cff9cd">Simple developer tool =
for extracting information from CloudStreams Provider Packages (with Extens=
ions), running on Integration Server.</p>
<div class=3D"panel" style=3D"background-color: #FFEBE6;border-width: 1px;"=
>
<div class=3D"panelContent" style=3D"background-color: #FFEBE6;">
<p local-id=3D"a074968f-078b-47d8-922e-0e3094d00a82">CAUTION: This is stric=
tly for local internal usage and prototyping, not intended for production d=
eployment.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"4db3d745-b90e-4942-a8d7-3d307fa2a998" id=3D"AIEnablement-Co=
nnectorsMetadataStandarization-Pre-requisite">Pre-requisite</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"c1005f80-d50c-4149-b355-b9e6db52dadb">
<li local-id=3D"eddec768-8ef0-4339-8828-dc6b7673e55a">
<p local-id=3D"aea7b638-cdf4-427f-9c83-e2f0f247875f">Use Integration Server=
 11.x or above.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"26bb0dc8-26d5-4807-8940-c61ef0df323e">
<p local-id=3D"06808016-dd29-48b4-b87e-58b646437bf7">Install WmCloudStreams=
 and WmCloudStreamsExt packages, with require CloudStreams Provider and Ext=
ension packages for required connectors.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ffecb28c-525c-486b-a788-b932770b970e">
<p local-id=3D"1d10c200-bed1-4e1c-b72e-248c18ca52b6">Install the <img heigh=
t=3D"250" style=3D"margin: 2px; border: 1px solid #ddd; box-sizing: border-=
box; vertical-align: text-bottom;" src=3D"38989c4edf5876baa408e40e4ddca97a3=
2c4a925291872d412199c1f36d656e5" width=3D"250"> as a package on Integration=
 Server.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d8b771d7-d928-4e24-8009-b4c2c2028d72">
<p local-id=3D"6cdaa0e4-fc41-4606-b7ce-376e6f3e75ce">Replace the <code>&lt;=
user&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;password&gt;</code> with appropriate user and=
 password for the Integration Server, before running the below commands</p>=
</li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"f1b4dc09-9788-439b-815a-0fcf7f1503a5"><strong>Sample Command=
s</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"545cacbb-b7cd-4a8e-90a9-951420e7c664">
<li local-id=3D"9f69709e-3ec3-48f9-909c-cd80ead7d141">
<p local-id=3D"7e62b18b-e6b1-4923-83e8-87a6ebe72596">For working with the i=
nternal tools, to fine-tune the introspection. Refer the GitHub repository =
here.</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"># List =
all provider packages installed on the Integration Server
curl -s "http://localhost:5555/c10s-providers" -u "&lt;user&gt;:&lt;passwor=
d&gt;" -H "Accept: application/json" | jq .

# List all connectors installed on the Integration Server
curl -s "http://localhost:5555/c10s-connectors" -u "&lt;user&gt;:&lt;passwo=
rd&gt;" -H "Accept: application/json" | jq .

# List all pre-defined operations defined for a given provider, across all =
enabled connectors
curl -s "http://localhost:5555/c10s-operations?packageName=3DWmServiceNowPr=
ovider" -u "&lt;user&gt;:&lt;password&gt;" -H "Accept: application/json" | =
jq .

# List all pre-defined operations defined for a given provider and connecto=
rId
curl -s "http://localhost:5555/c10s-operations?packageName=3DWmServiceNowPr=
ovider&amp;connectorId=3Dcom.softwareag.cloudstreams.servicenow_sandiego" -=
u "&lt;user&gt;:&lt;password&gt;" -H "Accept: application/json" | jq .
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h1 local-id=3D"ee92e9c4-b646-40f2-80f7-4c8984e6b78d" id=3D"AIEnablement-Co=
nnectorsMetadataStandarization-SampleResources">Sample Resources</h1>
<p local-id=3D"da618b1e-3bd4-4891-b700-1be9810e3bab">As part of preliminary=
 exercise of supporting identified use-cases (refer <a href=3D"https://ibm-=
middleware.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/~inkde/pages/135892493/AI+Enablement+-=
+Connectors+Metadata+Standarization#References" rel=3D"nofollow">References=
 </a>section), a sample response with connector metadata against Jira (trig=
gers from Node.js, actions from CloudStreams), ServiceNow (CloudStreams) an=
d Slack (Node.js) is attached below, for review and suitability assessment =
for AI.</p>
